==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Horopter
<hw>Ho*rop"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ boundary +
<?/ one who looks.]</ety> <fld>(Opt.)</fld> <def>The line or surface in
which are situated all the points which are seen single while the point
of sight, or the adjustment of the eyes, remains unchanged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sum of all the points which are seen single, while the point
of sight remains unchanged, is called the <qex>horopter</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Le Conte.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horopteric</ent>⟦br⟧
